VG. JAYAKUMARThe 15th Aravindan Puraskaram, instituted by the Chalachitra Film Society, was given to film director Albert for his maiden film `Kannemadanguka.' The film was chosen for "its closeness to life faced by the lower strata of society."Flute recitalThe award ceremony at Kalabhavan Theatre in Thiruvanthapuram,  was followed by a 90-minute flute recital by Mysore A. Chandan Kumar.The flautist began his recital with the famous Tyagaraja kriti `Entharo mahanu bhavalu' in Sree ragam set to Adi talam. `Vara narada Narayana,' again a Tyagaraja kriti, in Vijayasree followed next. He then played Swati Tirunal's `Gopalaka pahimam anisham' in Revagupthi.Chandan Kumar played Narayana Theerthar's tarangam `Govardanagiri dhare' in Darbarikanada, basically a Hindustani raga different from the Carnatic raga Kanada in the use ofdhaivatham.Chandan regaled listeners with a ragamalika comprising the ragas, Renjini, Sreerenjini, Megharenjini and Janarenjini. The kriti was `Renjini mrudu pankaja lochani' composed by Tanjavur Sankara Iyer. The flautist brought to fore the distinctive qualities of the four ragas.In the thaniavarthanam, Uduppi Balakrishnan and Karthikeyan provided the accompaniment on the mridangam and the ghatam respectively.The last piece of the evening was a tillana composed by Lalgudi G. Jayaram in Revathi set to misrachappu talam.Avaneeswaram S.R. Vinu did a commendable job, ably supporting the flautist on the violin. The great grandson of the violin maestro Mysore T. Chowdiah and disciple of M. Gopal Krishna, Chandan Kumar is an A-grade artiste with All India Radio.Bottom Template Starts
